01:44:16,000 --> 01:44:19,000
Look... Look at this.

962
01:44:19,000 --> 01:44:22,000
Music and movement.

963
01:44:22,000 --> 01:44:25,000
[ Crying ]

964
01:44:25,000 --> 01:44:29,000
Oh... Oh, for heaven's sake,

965
01:44:29,000 --> 01:44:32,000
stop... crying.

966
01:44:38,000 --> 01:44:42,000
**

967
01:44:42,000 --> 01:44:45,000
** [ Cello ]

968
01:45:48,000 --> 01:45:51,000
** [ Continues ]

969
01:46:12,000 --> 01:46:14,000
** [ Stops ]

970
01:46:17,000 --> 01:46:19,000
[ Sobbing ]

971
01:46:26,000 --> 01:46:29,000
<i>[ Wind Howling ]</i>

972
01:46:33,000 --> 01:46:35,000
[ Grunting ]

973
01:46:38,000 --> 01:46:40,000
I don't understand
what she wants.

974
01:46:41,000 --> 01:46:43,000
I think she's in
some sort of pain.

975
01:46:47,000 --> 01:46:51,000
There are things you
want to say. I can see that.

976
01:46:51,000 --> 01:46:55,000
But you cannot say them. Or
we cannot understand them.

977
01:46:55,000 --> 01:46:58,000
But there is someone
who hears your thoughts.

978
01:46:58,000 --> 01:47:02,000
Do not worry. God hears them
all. He hears your every thought.

979
01:47:02,000 --> 01:47:04,000
[ Screams ]

980
01:47:06,000 --> 01:47:08,000
[ Gasps ]

981
01:47:13,000 --> 01:47:15,000
Yes?

982
01:47:15,000 --> 01:47:18,000
Oh, it's Hilary,
Jacqueline's sister.

983
01:47:19,000 --> 01:47:22,000
Oh,
I see. This is my brother Piers.

984
01:47:22,000 --> 01:47:25,000
- Hello. <i>- [ People Chattering ]</i>

985
01:47:25,000 --> 01:47:30,000
Isn't this shocking
weather? Yes.

986
01:47:30,000 --> 01:47:32,000
Well, where's she going?

987
01:47:33,000 --> 01:47:35,000
<i>[ Chattering Continues ]</i>

988
01:47:50,000 --> 01:47:53,000
<i>[ Man Laughing ]</i>

989
01:48:10,000 --> 01:48:14,000
[ Grunting ] I can't get anything
down. I've been trying for days.

990
01:48:22,000 --> 01:48:24,000
Can I try?

991
01:48:45,000 --> 01:48:48,000
Shh, shh, shh. That's it.

992
01:48:52,000 --> 01:48:56,000
That's it. Up you go. Up you go.

993
01:48:56,000 --> 01:48:58,000
Come on.

994
01:48:59,000 --> 01:49:04,000
<i>[ Door Opens, Closes ]</i>

995
01:49:07,000 --> 01:49:10,000
Got you where I want you now.

996
01:49:10,000 --> 01:49:12,000
Come on.

997
01:49:18,000 --> 01:49:22,000
[ Blows Raspberry ]

998
01:49:22,000 --> 01:49:26,000
You're still in there somewhere then,
Jacks, huh?

999
01:49:31,000 --> 01:49:33,000
Come on.

1000
01:49:36,000 --> 01:49:40,000
Eh? You still in
there somewhere?

1001
01:49:40,000 --> 01:49:42,000
[ Panting ]

1002
01:49:48,000 --> 01:49:49,000
Good girl.

1003
01:49:56,000 --> 01:49:57,000
Good girl.

1004
01:50:01,000 --> 01:50:03,000
When you love someone,

1005
01:50:03,000 --> 01:50:08,000
pictures of them stay with
you all the time in your heart.

1006
01:50:08,000 --> 01:50:12,000
Pictures of the way you think
of them when you think of them.

1007
01:50:12,000 --> 01:50:16,000
With Mummy, it's that day
you broke the drum at the BBC.

1008
01:50:16,000 --> 01:50:19,000
Whenever you think
you've lost that person,

1009
01:50:19,000 --> 01:50:24,000
you start with a picture and
then you find them again.

1010
01:50:24,000 --> 01:50:28,000
Do you want to know what I
think of when I think of you?

1011
01:50:28,000 --> 01:50:31,000
When people say
"Jacqueline Du Pre" to me,

1012
01:50:31,000 --> 01:50:36,000
I think of a day on the
beach a long time ago,

1013
01:50:36,000 --> 01:50:39,000
long before you
could play the cello.

1014
01:50:39,000 --> 01:50:43,000
Before that Jacqueline
Du Pre or this one.

1015
01:50:45,000 --> 01:50:48,000
And we were playing a game.

1016
01:50:51,000 --> 01:50:56,000
When I was but 13 or so,

1017
01:50:56,000 --> 01:50:59,000
I went into a golden land.

1018
01:50:59,000 --> 01:51:05,000
Chimbarozo Cotopaxi
took me by the hand.

1019
01:51:05,000 --> 01:51:08,000
Over the Orinoco.

1020
01:51:08,000 --> 01:51:11,000
Across the blazing
Kalahari Desert.

1021
01:51:11,000 --> 01:51:15,000
Through the untamed grasslands
of the Veldt. Over the steppes...

1022
01:51:17,000 --> 01:51:19,000
And home.

1023
01:51:21,000 --> 01:51:25,000
Do you remember what you
said to me that day, Jackie?

1024
01:51:28,000 --> 01:51:33,000
You said... that everything
was going to be all right.

1025
01:51:38,000 --> 01:51:41,000
And in the end it was.

1026
01:51:59,000 --> 01:52:02,000
<i>[ Man ] ...hundreds of
roads were blocked...</i>

1027
01:52:02,000 --> 01:52:05,000
<i>and large parts of the rail
network are out of action.</i>

1028
01:52:05,000 --> 01:52:08,000
<i>The Home Secretary is chairing
an emergency meeting of ministers...</i>

1029
01:52:08,000 --> 01:52:11,000
<i>to discuss ways of
dealing with the emergency.</i>

1030
01:52:11,000 --> 01:52:15,000
<i>The cellist Jacqueline Du Pre
has died at her London home.</i>

1031
01:52:15,000 --> 01:52:18,000
<i>She was 42.</i>

1032
01:52:18,000 --> 01:52:22,000
<i>Jacqueline Du Pre began to
learn the cello at the age of five...</i>

1033
01:52:22,000 --> 01:52:26,000
<i>and won several awards before
rising to the top of her profession.</i>

1034
01:52:26,000 --> 01:52:31,000
<i>She will be particularly remembered for
her performances of Elgar's</i> Cello Concerto.

1035
01:52:33,000 --> 01:52:35,000
Stop the car, Piers.

1036
01:52:35,000 --> 01:52:37,000
<i>Stop the car.</i>

1037
01:52:48,000 --> 01:52:50,000
Oh, God!

1038
01:52:50,000 --> 01:52:54,000
[ Sobbing ] Jackie!

1039
01:52:58,000 --> 01:53:00,000
Hils, where are you going?

1040
01:53:08,000 --> 01:53:11,000
<i>[ Hilary ] When I
was but 13 or so,</i>

1041
01:53:11,000 --> 01:53:15,000
<i>I went into a golden land.</i>

1042
01:53:15,000 --> 01:53:19,000
<i>Chimbarozo Cotopaxi
took me by the hand.</i>

1043
01:53:21,000 --> 01:53:24,000
<i>Over the Orinoco.</i>

1044
01:53:24,000 --> 01:53:27,000
<i>Across the blazing
Kalahari desert.</i>

1045
01:53:27,000 --> 01:53:31,000
<i>Through the untamed
grasslands of the Veldt.</i>

1046
01:53:31,000 --> 01:53:34,000
<i>Over the steppes...</i>

1047
01:53:34,000 --> 01:53:36,000
<i>And home.</i>

1048
01:53:50,000 --> 01:53:52,000
What do you want?

1049
01:53:52,000 --> 01:53:56,000
Nothing. Just to see you.

1050
01:53:56,000 --> 01:53:58,000
Bye.

1051
01:53:58,000 --> 01:54:00,000
Jackie.

1052
01:54:02,000 --> 01:54:04,000
I just wanted to tell you...

1053
01:54:04,000 --> 01:54:08,000
that everything's
going to be all right.

